    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a driver-focused 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L high-output straight-six. This powerplant utilizes six individual throttle bodies and double VANOS variable valve timing to deliver a linear power band and a 7,900 RPM redline. The chassis remains structurally sound with documented rear subframe reinforcement\u2014a critical preventative measure for this platform. Power is delivered through a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a factory M-variable differential lock, ensuring optimal torque vectoring. This example has been maintained with an emphasis on mechanical longevity, including a recent valve clearance adjustment and cooling system overhaul. While the aesthetic reflects honest road use, the kinematic integrity of the suspension is preserved via refreshed bushings and dampers, offering the precise steering rack feedback and turn-in characteristics expected of the marque.",
